             Sojitz Corp. and Thompson Creek
Metals Co. will invest C$500 million ($492 million) to increase
production at the Endako molybdenum mine in Canadaâ€™s British
Columbia.  
 The expansion will increase annual production to 16 million
pounds after 2011, from 10 million pounds currently, the
Japanese company said today in a statement on its website.  
